    "body": "Hello @Yuhana-sr \r\n\r\nIf what you mean is that you want a token to be pegged/backed by another token then you are looking for our [ERC20Wrapper contract](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/extensions/ERC20Wrapper.sol). This can be used to wrap `SomeToken` into `XSomeToken`.\r\n\r\nIf you are talking about having a fixed price against a non-crypto asset, like ‚Ç¨ or $, then you are into the \"stable coin\" territory. There are a lot of these, with varying designs. It is a very difficult thing to get right (as recent actuality showed) and is way beyond the scope of this repo.",
